        <main>
            <section id="about">
                <h2>About</h2>
                <p>The Genome Data Management System is a database system designed to store and manage gene and protein data along with their corresponding nucleotide and protein sequences.</p>
            </section>

            <section id="features">
                <h2>Features</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Store gene and protein information including names and descriptions.</li>
                    <li>Store nucleotide and protein sequence data.</li>
                    <li>Establish links between genes and proteins.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section id="installation">
                <h2>Installation</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Clone this repository to your local machine.</li>
                    <li>Execute the <code>ddl.sql</code> script in your preferred SQL database management system to create the necessary tables.</li>
                    <li>You may populate the tables with sample data for testing purposes using the provided <code>sample_data.sql</code> script.</li>
                    <li>Start using the system to manage your genome data.</li>
                </ol>
            </section>

            <section id="usage">
                <h2>Usage</h2>
                <p>Use the provided SQL queries to interact with the database and perform operations such as inserting, updating, and querying data. Ensure proper handling of foreign key constraints when linking genes and proteins.</p>
            </section>

            <!-- Form for inserting gene and protein data -->
            <section id="insert">
                <h2>Insert Gene and Protein Data</h2>
                <form action="index.php" method="post">
                    <label for="gene_name">Gene Name:</label><br>
                    <input type="text" id="gene_name" name="gene_name" required><br>
                    <label for="nucleotide_sequence">Nucleotide Sequence:</label><br>
                    <textarea id="nucleotide_sequence" name="nucleotide_sequence" required></textarea><br>
                    <label for="protein_name">Protein Name:</label><br>
                    <input type="text" id="protein_name" name="protein_name" required><br>
                    <label for="protein_sequence">Protein Sequence:</label><br>
                    <textarea id="protein_sequence" name="protein_sequence" required></textarea><br>
                    <input type="submit" value="Submit">
                </form>
            </section>

